      bearCase: "The technical hurdles of blockchain (scalability, efficiency, energy consumption) are too significant for meaningful AI integration in the near term. The \'crypto-AI\' narrative is primarily hype, risking a new speculative bubble and misallocation of capital, with little practical utility for mainstream AI applications.",
      neutralCase: "While broad integration of blockchain into core AI infrastructure is unlikely currently, niche applications (e.g., data provenance, specific incentive layers) could emerge. The long-term potential requires significant technical advancements in both fields, and adoption will be gradual and highly specialized.",
