      neutralCase: "The crypto market is in a phase of dynamic evolution, balancing innovation with necessary regulatory and security measures. While positive steps are being made in stablecoin regulation and future-proof technology, immediate cybersecurity risks continue to challenge user safety. The overall trajectory points towards a more mature but also more complex ecosystem, where both opportunities and threats are amplified.",
      probabilityWeightedOutlook: "There is a moderate to high probability that regulatory frameworks will continue to mature, driving institutional interest and the development of more compliant crypto products. The probability of significant quantum computing threats materializing in the short-to-medium term (next 5 years) remains low but necessitates proactive measures. The probability of ongoing and evolving cybersecurity threats is very high, requiring continuous user education and technological defenses. Overall, the market is likely to trend towards greater security and regulation, but with persistent, albeit manageable, risks.",
