      probabilityWeightedOutlook: "A neutral-to-bearish outlook holds higher probability in the near term (3-6 months). The strength of the \'higher-for-longer\' macro signal from the bond market, coupled with Bitcoin\'s \'damaged\' technical trend and regulatory risks, outweighs the current bullish bounce. A significant shift in Fed policy or a strong, independent technical breakout would be required to shift this weighting.",
      potentialCatalysts: ["Unexpected dovish pivot by the Federal Reserve.", "Bitcoin decisively breaking and holding above $61,775-$63,850.", "Increased institutional adoption or new Bitcoin ETF products.", "Significant geopolitical events driving demand for decentralized assets.", "Major technological upgrades or widespread adoption of Bitcoin Layer 2 solutions."],
      keyRisks: ["Persistent high inflation forcing the Fed to maintain restrictive policy.", "Economic recession leading to broader risk-off sentiment.", "Technical breakdown below $59,100, triggering cascading liquidations.", "Unfavorable regulatory actions or outright bans in major jurisdictions.", "Major security vulnerabilities or hacks impacting investor confidence."],
