    executiveSummary: "The market reacted to Lorie Logan\'s speech with stocks weakening modestly, the U.S. dollar and front-end Treasury yields surging, and precious metals coming under additional pressure. The Dow deteriorated the most, while the Russell 2000 gave back most of its gains. The FX market delivered the clearest verdict with broad-based U.S. dollar buying. The 2-year yield rose over 4 basis points, the strongest move on the board, indicating that the market priced in a more restrictive Fed policy.",
    marketBackground: "Lorie Logan, the Fed\'s vice chair for supervision, delivered a speech on Tuesday, sparking market reactions. The overall takeaway was that the market interpreted the Fed as more hawkish than expected.",
    detailedAnalysis: "# Market Reaction\n\n## Stocks\n\n- The Dow deteriorated the most during the press conference, losing 104 points.\n- The Russell 2000 gave back most of its gains, ending the day up just 0.03%.\n- The Nasdaq actually recovered slightly, suggesting technology shares held up relatively well despite rising yields.\n\nOverall equity reaction was negative but not disorderly.\n\n## Foreign Exchange\n\n- The FX market delivered the clearest verdict with broad-based U.S. dollar buying.\n- The largest dollar gains came against GBP, EUR, NZD, and CHF.\n- The market appears to have pushed back expectations for future Fed easing.\n\n## Treasury Yields\n\n- The move was concentrated in the front end of the curve, with the 2-year yield rising over 4 basis points, the strongest move on the board.\n- The yield curve flattened as long-end yields barely moved, indicating classic pricing for \'The Fed may stay restrictive longer\'.\n\n## Commodities & Crypto\n\n- Gold and silver came under pressure, with gold losing $28 and silver losing $0.68.\n- Bitcoin also lost $217, trading around $65,190.\n\n# Crypto Industry Developments\n\n## Blockchain.com Expands Tokenized Equities\n\nBlockchain.com, in collaboration with Ondo Finance, is broadening access to tokenized traditional assets as demand for onchain stocks and ETFs continues to grow.\n\n## Coinbase Diversifies Revenue Streams\n\nCoinbase is shifting from reliance on bitcoin-linked trading revenue toward a broader financial platform spanning derivatives, tokenized stocks, stablecoin payments, lending, and artificial intelligence. Analysts see derivatives as the key opportunity, with options and perpetual futures accounting for most global crypto trading volume. Stablecoins, developer tools, and early-stage AI products are viewed as emerging, less volatile revenue streams that may not move near-term earnings but signal Coinbase\'s widening earnings base and long-term growth prospects.",
    expertInsights: "Analysts believe that Coinbase\'s push into derivatives, payments, and infrastructure broadens its growth story beyond crypto trading. They see derivatives as the key opportunity, with options and perpetual futures accounting for most global crypto trading volume.",
